---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy - Stuga" description="Privacy Policy for the Stuga Home Assistant Dashboard app.">
  <!-- Navigation -->
  <nav class="fixed top-0 left-0 right-0 z-50 bg-background/80 backdrop-blur-md border-b border-border">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-4 flex items-center justify-between">
      <a href="/" class="flex items-center gap-3">
        <img src="/icon.png" alt="Stuga" class="w-8 h-8 rounded-lg" />
        <span class="font-bold text-lg">Stuga</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <main class="pt-32 pb-20 px-6">
    <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto prose prose-neutral dark:prose-invert">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-muted mb-12">Last updated: January 2026</p>

      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Overview</h2>
        <p class="text-muted leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Stuga is a Home Assistant dashboard app developed by Twinbolt AB. We are committed to
          protecting your privacy. This policy explains how Stuga handles your data.
        </p>
        <p class="text-muted leading-relaxed">
          <strong class="text-foreground">The short version:</strong> Stuga runs entirely on your device and connects
          directly to your Home Assistant instance. We collect anonymous crash reports to improve stability, but no personal data or Home Assistant information is ever collected.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Data Collection</h2>
        <p class="text-muted leading-relaxed mb-4">
          <strong class="text-foreground">Stuga collects minimal anonymous data to improve app stability.</strong> The app operates locally on your
          device and communicates only with your Home Assistant server for smart home control.
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-muted space-y-2">
          <li>Anonymous crash reports via Firebase Crashlytics (to fix bugs)</li>
          <li>No personal information or Home Assistant data is collected</li>
          <li>No usage analytics or behavioral tracking</li>
          <li>No advertising or ad tracking</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Data Storage</h2>
        <p class="text-muted leading-relaxed mb-4">
          All data is stored locally on your device:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-muted space-y-2">
          <li><strong class="text-foreground">Home Assistant URL:</strong> Stored in local storage on your device</li>
          <li><strong class="text-foreground">Authentication tokens:</strong> Stored securely in your device's keychain (iOS) or keystore (Android)</li>
          <li><strong class="text-foreground">App preferences:</strong> Stored locally on your device</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-muted leading-relaxed mt-4">
          On the web version, data is stored in your browser's local storage. No data is sent to our servers.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Network Communication</h2>
        <p class="text-muted leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Stuga only communicates with:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-muted space-y-2">
          <li><strong class="text-foreground">Your Home Assistant instance:</strong> To fetch device states and send commands</li>
          <li><strong class="text-foreground">Fontshare (Google CDN):</strong> To load the Satoshi font</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-muted leading-relaxed mt-4">
          All communication with your Home Assistant server uses the authentication method you choose
          (OAuth or long-lived access token). Your credentials are never shared with Twinbolt AB or any third party.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p class="text-muted leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Stuga uses the following third-party services:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-muted space-y-2">
          <li><strong class="text-foreground">Firebase Crashlytics:</strong> For anonymous crash reporting to help us fix bugs. No personal data is collected.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-foreground">Fontshare CDN:</strong> For loading the Satoshi font.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-muted leading-relaxed mt-4">
          Stuga does not use any advertising, behavioral analytics, or user tracking services.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Open Source</h2>
        <p class="text-muted leading-relaxed">
          Stuga is open source. You can review the complete source code at
          <a href="https://github.com/twinbolt-ab/stuga" class="text-accent hover:underline">github.com/twinbolt-ab/stuga</a>
          to verify our privacy practices.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p class="text-muted leading-relaxed">
          Stuga does not collect any personal information from anyone, including children under 13.
          The app is rated 4+ and is suitable for all ages.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p class="text-muted leading-relaxed">
          We may update this privacy policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page
          with an updated revision date.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Contact Us</h2>
        <p class="text-muted leading-relaxed mb-4">
          If you have questions about this privacy policy, please contact us:
        </p>
        <p class="text-muted">
          <strong class="text-foreground">Twinbolt AB</strong><br />
          Sweden<br />
          <a href="https://github.com/twinbolt-ab/stuga/issues" class="text-accent hover:underline">GitHub Issues</a>
        </p>
      </section>
    </article>
  </main>

  <!-- Footer -->
  <footer class="py-12 px-6 border-t border-border">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center justify-between gap-6">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
        <img src="/icon.png" alt="Stuga" class="w-6 h-6 rounded-md" />
        <span class="text-muted text-sm">&copy; 2026 Twinbolt AB</span>
      </div>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-6 text-sm">
        <a href="/" class="text-muted hover:text-foreground transition-colors">Home</a>
        <a href="/blog" class="text-muted hover:text-foreground transition-colors">Blog</a>
        <a href="https://github.com/twinbolt-ab/stuga" class="text-muted hover:text-foreground transition-colors">GitHub</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </footer>
</Layout>

<style>
  .prose h2 {
    @apply text-foreground;
  }
  .prose strong {
    @apply text-foreground;
  }
</style>
